TITLE: Cross-Platform URI Handler Implementation
DESCRIPTION: Implementation of a singleton class that handles URI storage and listening across different platforms.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jetbrains/kotlin-multiplatform-dev-docs/blob/master/topics/compose/compose-navigation-deep-links.md#2025-04-23_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
object ExternalUriHandler {
    // Storage for when a URI arrives before the listener is set up
    private var cached: String? = null

    var listener: ((uri: String) -> Unit)? = null
        set(value) {
            field = value
            if (value != null) {
                // When a listener is set and `cached` is not empty,
                // immediately invoke the listener with the cached URI
                cached?.let { value.invoke(it) }
                cached = null
            }
        }

    // When a new URI arrives, cache it.
    // If the listener is already set, invoke it and clear the cache immediately.
    fun onNewUri(uri: String) {
        cached = uri
        listener?.let {
            it.invoke(uri)
            cached = null
        }
    }
}
```

