TITLE: Implementing loadLaunches Method for SpaceX Data Fetching in Kotlin
DESCRIPTION: Adds a loadLaunches function to the RocketLaunchViewModel that fetches rocket launch data asynchronously using coroutines. It updates the view state to reflect loading status and handles exceptions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jetbrains/kotlin-multiplatform-dev-docs/blob/master/topics/development/multiplatform-ktor-sqldelight.md#2025-04-23_snippet_25

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
import androidx.lifecycle.viewModelScope
import kotlinx.coroutines.launch

class RocketLaunchViewModel(private val sdk: SpaceXSDK) : ViewModel() {
    //...

    fun loadLaunches() {
        viewModelScope.launch { 
            _state.value = _state.value.copy(isLoading = true, launches = emptyList())
            try {
                val launches = sdk.getLaunches(forceReload = true)
                _state.value = _state.value.copy(isLoading = false, launches = launches)
            } catch (e: Exception) {
                _state.value = _state.value.copy(isLoading = false, launches = emptyList())
            }
        }
    }
}
